). Two lobes located on the cymbial distal margin retrolaterally. The small lobe near the ventral side, semicircular or triangular, with a single seta or without. The large lobe close to the dorsal side, with at least a strong, thickened, closely appressed setae. There are also some other strong setae on the subdistal end of cymbium retrolaterally (
<figureCitation box="[608,691,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-26@16.[151,1435,181,1693]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 16. Cymbium apophysis of Ectatosticta left male palp, prolateral view. A. E. bajie Lin &amp; Li, 2021; B. E. davidi (Simon, 1889); C. E. deltshevi Platnick &amp; Jäger, 2009; D. E. nyingchiensis sp. nov.; E. E. pingwuensis sp. nov.; F–G. E. rulai Lin &amp; Li, 2021 (F from Jiuzhaigou, G from Wanglang); H. E. shennongjiaensis sp. nov.; I. E. songpanensis sp. nov.; J. E. wukong Lin &amp; Li, 2020; K. E. yukuni Lin &amp; Li, 2021. Abbreviations: CL, cymbial lobe; TS, thickened setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5222613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5222613/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Embolus and conductor located on the genital bulb apically. Embolus thin, relatively long and arc-curved, with a wide base. Conductor lamellar, slightly clockwise curved, holding the apical part of embolus. The bases of embolus and conductor combined together.
</paragraph>
